					<div class='comment-content'>I am so glad to have access to this article. I am transitioning to a Quality Improvement Coordinator this coming September. This article gave me an idea of how to go about a QI Project. I am new to this field and to Lean &amp; Six Sigma except for what I have learned from my Master's class in Quality Improvement, especially from the clinical portion of this class. I did present an Operating Room Poster in a QI Fair after that class. I like the part where you have to get the people involved excited about the project and to continuously assess the usefulness and success of the project. Thank you very much.</div>
